``\r\n\r\nIn method BaseActiveRecord::refresh() we got:\r\n```\r\n$record = static::findOne($this->getPrimaryKey(true));\r\n```\r\n\r\nmethod BaseActiveRecord::getPrimaryKey(true) return array ['id' => 1]\r\nand we got ambiguous column 'id'\r\n\r\nP.S.: sorry for my english :)\r\n\r\n### What is the expected result?\r\n\r\nduplicate refresh() method in ActiveRecord class\r\nand replace\r\n\r\n```\r\npublic function refresh()\r\n{\r\n\t$query = static::find();\r\n\tif (!empty($query->join) || !empty($query->joinWith)) {\r\n\t\t$condition = [];\r\n\t\tforeach ($this->getPrimaryKey(true) as $column=>$value){\r\n\t\t\t$condition[static::tableName() . '.' . $column] = $value;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t} else {\r\n\t\t$condition = $this->getPrimaryKey(true);\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\t/* @var $record BaseActiveRecord */\r\n\t$record = static::findOne($condition);\r\n\tif ($record === null) {\r\n\t\treturn false;\r\n\t}\r\n\tforeach ($this->attributes() as $name) {\r\n\t\t$this->_attributes[$name] = isset($record->_attributes[$name]) ? $record->_attributes[$name] : null;\r\n\t}\r\n\t$this->_oldAttributes = $record->_oldAttributes;\r\n\t$this->_related = [];\r\n\t$this->afterRefresh();\r\n\r\n\treturn true;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What do you get instead?\r\nSQL error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nSQLSTATE[23000]: Integrity constraint violation: 1052 Column 'id' in where clause is ambiguous\r\nThe SQL being executed was: SELECT `training_module`.* FROM `training_module` INNER JOIN `training_category` ON `training_module`.`training_category_id` = `training_category`.`id` WHERE (`id`=15) AND (`training_category`.`training_id`=1)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Additional info\r\n\r\n| Q                | A\r\n| ---------------- | ---\r\n| Yii version      | 2.0.11.2\r\n| PHP version      | 7.0\r\n| Operating system | Ubuntu 16.04\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"cebe","id":189796,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4OTc5Ng==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/189796?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/cebe"